## Guidelines
- Each beat should expand into 1-3 scenes depending on complexity
- Scene headings must follow standard format: INT./EXT. LOCATION - TIME
- Action lines should be in present tense, concise and vivid
- Dialogue should be character-specific (each character has a distinguishable voice)
- Include parentheticals sparingly and only when necessary
- The screenplay should be approximately 90-120 pages (use estimated_page_range to track)
- Maintain consistency with character descriptions from the character registry
- Include visual direction in action lines (lighting, mood, camera notes)
- Ensure proper pacing: setup (1-25 pages), confrontation (25-85 pages), resolution (85-110 pages)
